=comment -----------------------------------------------------------------------
=head3 color-set

Emitted when the user selects a color.

When handling this signal, use L<.get-rgba() in class ColorChooser|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/ColorChooser#get-rgba>
to find out which color was just selected.

Note that this signal is only emitted when the user changes the color.
If you need to react to programmatic color changes as well, use
the notify::rgba signal.

=begin code
method handler (
  Int :$_handle_id,
  N-GObject :$_native-object,
  Gnome::Gtk4::ColorButton :$_widget,
  *%user-options
)
=end code

=item $_handle_id; The registered event handler id.
=item $_native-object; The native object provided by the Raku object which registered this event. This is a native B<Gnome::Gtk4::ColorButton> object.
